import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rates across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    year = 2000
    year_data = data[data['year'] == year]
    year_data = year_data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    top_industries = year_data['series'].head(10)
    year_data = year_data[year_data['series'].isin(top_industries)]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(year_data['series'], year_data['rate'])
    ax.set_title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in ' + str(year) + '?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Industry')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rates across all industries?', wrap=True)

        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot(data['rate'].groupby(data['date'].dt.month).apply(list), showfliers=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('How does the unemployment rate vary across different months of the year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))

    plt.scatter(data['count'], data['rate'])
    plt.xlabel('Number of Unemployed People')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of unemployed people and the unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
